fields.name: photo-log-import-operator
fields.description:
For the purposes of adding legacy metadata from the spreadsheet named 'master photo log,' this import field indicates data found in the column marked 'operator.' 

Note that this column was used inconsistently. Sometimes it does indicate a scanning operator, but other times it indicates a source or other information.

fields.name: photo-log-import-description
fields.description:
For the purposes of adding legacy metadata from the spreadsheet named 'master photo log,' this import field indicates data found in the column marked 'subject.' 

Note that this column was used inconsistently. Many times it is used as a freestyle description of the item, other times it lists subjects or people or places in the photo.

fields.name: linked Item ID#
fields.description: Used only for CSV imports and batch update functions

fields.name: photo-log-import-source
fields.description:
For the purposes of adding legacy metadata from the spreadsheet named 'master photo log,' this import field indicates data found in the column marked 'source.' 

Note that this column was used inconsistently. Sometimes it does indicate a source, but other times it indicates a scanning operator or other information.

fields.name: photo-log-import-year
fields.description:
For the purposes of adding legacy metadata from the spreadsheet named 'master photo log,' this import field indicates data found in the column marked 'year.' 

Note that this column was used inconsistently. Sometimes it does indicate a year formatted YYYY, but other times it indicates a range or decade, i.e. 1970/80s.

fields.name: photo-log-import-event
fields.description:
For the purposes of adding legacy metadata from the spreadsheet named 'master photo log,' this import field indicates data found in the column marked 'occasion.' 

Note that this column was used inconsistently. Many times it is used to indicate an event or occasion. Other times it is a freestyle description of the item, and other times it lists subjects or people or places in the photo.

fields.name: photo-log-import-location
fields.description: For the purposes of adding legacy metadata from the spreadsheet named 'master photo log,' this import field indicates data found in the column marked 'location.'
